Dear colleagues,

the customer needs to know the current export setup to decide about changes that have to be done based on the recommendation of Doreen below:
 * export on location level:
all locations with day / time / export interval
 * export on system level:
locations included in the export on system level with day / time / export interval   

Background is the following:
the customer reported that e.g. in exports  491081 and 491082 the same statements were exported.

 

Outcome of https://jira.ifao.net/browse/ITE-1620 (Holtzbrinck - statements are included in two exports with same export time):

{{+*Root Cause:*+}}
{{There are two Exports starting at the same time}}
{{One job is Starting for Location, the other job is starting for System. }}

!image-2023-04-04-21-11-56-068.png|width=1076,height=106!

 

{{From the visible jobs, there is no job that can be seen for System, however, the jobs sometimes show a Location parameter, but it is not stored. This is the reason why the jobs for the Locations should not start at the same time.}} 
 
{{+*Solution:*+}}
{{Remove all Export jobs and set them up again. Make sure no jobs run in parallel which is currently the case for some of the jobs}}

 

Thank you in advance and best regards,

Annette

